p-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-28-2020.html|archive-date=March 2, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary = When a building explodes in a village in Germany, Mac discovers the cause was a defective time-release bomb from World War II. Mac finds another bomb that hasn't been detonated yet, so he and Riley try to extract it without setting it off. Meanwhile, Desi works to save one of the victims in the rubble, while Russ is concerned about Bozer's role on the team. Mac finally finds out that Riley is dating someone. They also find out that the mysterious organization was established in the 1940s under the name \"CODEX\".\n |LineColor = 0B6138\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|MacGyver (2016 TV series, season 4)\n |EpisodeNumber = 71\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 5\n |Title = Soccer + Desi + Merchant + Titan\n |DirectedBy = [[Duane Clark]]\n |WrittenBy = Cindy Appel\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|6}}\n |ProdCode = MAC405\n |Viewers = 5.65<ref name=\"4.05\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-6-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.6.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 9, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 9, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311165332/http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-6-2020.html|archive-date=March 11, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary = The team finally plays offense against CODEX by planning to take down their source of income, \"The Merchant\", who rigs women's soccer games in [[Milan, Italy]]. Desi goes undercover as a member of the soccer team, and The Merchant takes the bait, asking her to throw the game. The team finds out that The Merchant is going to have a meeting with the leader of CODEX, \"Titan\". Russ wants to get to Titan, but things go bad when The Merchant plants an electronic chip in Desi that will electrocute her if she fails to intentionally miss a penalty kick. Mac devises a way to save Desi while the rest of the team tries to catch The Merchant and Titan. They save Desi, but The Merchant and Titan escape. In the end, they are shocked to learn that Titan appears to be Matty.\n |LineColor = 0B6138\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|MacGyver (2016 TV series, season 4)\n |EpisodeNumber = 72\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 6\n |Title = Right + Wrong + Both + Neither\n |DirectedBy = Roderick Davis\n |WrittenBy = Andrew Klein\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|13}}\n |ProdCode = MAC406\n |Viewers = 5.84<ref name=\"4.06\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-13-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.13.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 16, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 16, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317050913/http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-13-2020.html|archive-date=March 17, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary = The team determines that Matty is not \"Titan\", and they learn that CODEX hacked their servers to plant the fake evidence. While on a plane, Russ listens to a voicemail from his former love, Emilia ([[Amanda Schull]]), who asks him for help. He learns that Emilia was kidnapped by the same Eastern European rebels he fought during his military contract days. He then takes the Phoenix team to a small, impoverished town just across the Ukrainian border to rescue Emilia and rid the town of the rebels for good. In the end, the team saves Emilia, shuts down the rebels' illegal operation, and Russ pays the rebels to leave the town.\n |LineColor = 0B6138\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|MacGyver (2016 TV series, season 4)\n |EpisodeNumber = 73\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 7\n |Title = Mac + Desi + Riley + Aubrey\n |DirectedBy = 