on              = Promotional poster for the season\n| starring             = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Lucas Till]]\n* [[Tristin Mays]]\n* [[Justin Hires]]\n* [[Meredith Eaton]]\n*[[Levy Tran]]\n*[[Henry Ian Cusick]]\n}}\n| country              = United States\n| num_episodes         = 8<!--Only increment as a new episode premieres, per the documentation of the template.-->\n| network              = [[CBS]]\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2020|2|7}}<!--Do not add until season has premiered, per the documentation of the template.-->\n| last_aired           = {{End date|present}}<!--Do not add until season has premiered, per the documentation of the template.-->\n| episode_list         = List of MacGyver (2016 TV series) episodes\n}}\n\nThe fourth season of the [[CBS]] [[Action film#Action adventure|Action-adventure]] drama series ''[[MacGyver (2016 TV series)|MacGyver]]'' premiered on February 7, 2020 as a [[mid-season replacement]] for the [[2019\u201320 United States network television schedule|2019\u201320 television season]]. The series centers on the fictional [[Organizations in MacGyver#Phoenix Foundation|Phoenix Foundation]] which is a covert organization masquerading as a think tank. The series stars [[Lucas Till]], [[Tristin Mays]], [[Justin Hires]], [[Meredith Eaton]], [[Levy Tran]] and [[Henry Ian Cusick]].\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{main|List of MacGyver characters}}\n\n===Main===\n* [[Lucas Till]] as [[MacGyver|Angus \"Mac\" MacGyver]]\n* [[Tristin Mays]] as Riley Davis\n* [[Justin Hires]] as Wilt Bozer\n* [[Meredith Eaton]] as Matilda \"Matty\" Webber\n* [[Levy Tran]] as Desiree \"Desi\" Nguyen\n* [[Henry Ian Cusick]] as Russell \"Russ/Rusty\" Taylor\n\n===Recurring===\n*[[Leonardo Nam]] as Aubrey, Riley's boyfriend for a brief time\n*[[Tate Donovan]] as James \"Jimmy\" MacGyver/Oversight\n*[[Jeri Ryan]] as Gwendolyn \"Gwen\" Hayes, MacGyver's aunt (his mother\u2019s sister); an ex-DXS agent who was presumed dead, but is now head of CODEX.<ref>{{Cite