le-originals-network-finals-2-21-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.21.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=February 24, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=February 24, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224211957/http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-21-2020.html|archive-date=February 24, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary = While aboard their jet, MacGyver and the team discover a private plane in which the pilot, flying with his young son, has suffered a heart attack. Mac and Desi board the plane mid-flight, and discover that the medical emergency was intentional. During the rescue, Russ and Matty disagree over who has the ultimate authority to make critical judgment calls in an active operation. Russ later agrees that Matty is more qualified to do so.\n |LineColor = 0B6138\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|MacGyver (2016 TV series, season 4)\n |EpisodeNumber = 70\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 4\n |Title = Windmill + Acetone + Celluloid + Firing Pin\n |DirectedBy = [[Eagle Egilsson]] \n |WrittenBy = Andrew Karlsruher\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|2|28}}\n |ProdCode = MAC404\n |Viewers = 5.57<ref name=\"4.04\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-28-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 2.28.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 2, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 2, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302211748/http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-2-28-2020.html|archive-date=March 2, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary = When a building explodes in a village in Germany, Mac discovers the cause was a defective time-release bomb from World War II. Mac finds another bomb that hasn't been detonated yet, so he 