6138\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|MacGyver (2016 TV series, season 4)\n |EpisodeNumber = 72\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 6\n |Title = Right + Wrong + Both + Neither\n |DirectedBy = Roderick Davis\n |WrittenBy = Andrew Klein\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|13}}\n |ProdCode = MAC406\n |Viewers = 5.84<ref name=\"4.06\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-13-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.13.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 16, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 16, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317050913/http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-13-2020.html|archive-date=March 17, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary = The team determines that Matty is not \"Titan\", and they learn that CODEX hacked their servers to plant the fake evidence. While on a plane, Russ listens to a voicemail from his former love, Emilia ([[Amanda Schull]]), who asks him for help. He learns that Emilia was kidnapped by the same Eastern European rebels he fought during his military contract days. He then takes the Phoenix team to a small, impoverished town just across the Ukrainian border to rescue Emilia and rid the town of the rebels for good. In the end, the team saves Emilia, shuts down the rebels' illegal operation, and Russ pays the rebels to leave the town.\n |LineColor = 0B6138\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|MacGyver (2016 TV series, season 4)\n |EpisodeNumber = 73\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 7\n |Title = Mac + Desi + Riley + Aubrey\n |DirectedBy = [[Brad Turner (director)|Brad Turner]]\n |WrittenBy = Stephanie Hicks\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|27}}\n |ProdCode = MAC407\n |Viewers = 6.72<ref name=\"4.07\">{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-27-2020.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 3.27.2020|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|date=March 30, 2020|work=Showbuzz Daily|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary =  While on a double date with Riley and her boyfriend, Aubrey, Mac and Desi witness the murder of the restaurant owner by Chinese Triad hitmen. The hitmen kidnap Riley and Aubrey due to a $2 million debt, as Aubrey confesses to Riley that he co-owns the restaurant. After Aubrey sees his accounts have been emptied, Riley says she can use her hacking skills to locate the money. In the end, Aubrey breaks up with Riley over her dishonesty about her job, and she moves in with Mac. Meanwhile, Matty visits James MacGyver in his hospital room to tell him about the CODEX situation. He tells her to look up something called File 47, which he describes as \"the end of the world\".\n |LineColor = 0B6138\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|MacGyver (2016 TV series, season 4)\n |EpisodeNumber = 74\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 8\n |Title = Father + Son + Father + Matriarch\n |DirectedBy = David Straiton\n |WrittenBy = Travis Fickett\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|3}}\n |ProdCode = MAC408\n |Viewers = \n |ShortSummary = When Mason resurfaces, Mac and his father Jimmy must put aside their feud and catch him once and for all, but they soon realize it is a set up by CODEX, forcing all three to work together to escape. They get caught by CODEX and finally meet \"Titan\", which turns out to be Mac's aunt, Gwendolyn \"Gwen\" Hayes, a former DHX Agent thought to have been killed. She tries to persuade Mac to join her but it fails. Mason and Jimmy make a plan to destroy the place after Mac is safe, but Jimmy is forced to manually trigger the blast and is presumed dead. Mac survives alongside Mason, who then flees again. Meanwhile, The Phoenix is ambushed by the CIA, who found out Matty was inquiring about File 47. After thwarting the CIA, Matty finally tells the team about File 47, stating all who worked on it were presumed dead, except one which turns out to be Gwen.\n |LineColor = 0B6138\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|MacGyver (2016 TV series, season 4)\n |EpisodeNumber = 75\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 9\n |Title = Code + Artemis + Nuclear + N3mesis\n |RTitle = <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/listings/20200319cbs14/|title=(#MAC409) \"Code + Artemis + Nuclear + N3mesis\"|accessdate=March 20, 2020|work=[[The Futon Critic]]}}</ref>\n |DirectedBy = Michael Martinez\n |WrittenBy = Brandon Botta & Casey Tollett Botta<ref name=\"WGA\"/>\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|10}}\n |ProdCode = MAC409\n |Viewers = \n |ShortSummary =\n |LineColor = 0B6138\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|MacGyver (2016 TV series, season 4)\n |EpisodeNumber = 76\n |EpisodeNumber2 = 10\n |Title = Tesla + Bell + Edison + Mac\n |RTitle = <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/macgyver/listings/|title=macgyver on cbs|accessdate=March 20, 2020|work=[[The Futon Critic]]}}</ref>\n |DirectedBy = \n |WrittenBy = Rob Pearlstein<ref name=\"WGA\">{{Cite web |url=https://directories.wga.org/project/1116147/macgyver/ |title=MacGyver |website=[[Writers Guild of America West]] |access-date=February 1, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201021111/https://directories.wga.org/project/1116147/macgyver/ |archive-date=February 1, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|17}}\n |ProdCode = MAC410\n |Viewers = \n |ShortSummary =\n |LineColor = 0B6138\n}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\nEpisodes of the fourth season include:<ref name=\"WGA\"/>\n\n* \"Loyalty + Family + Rogue + Hellfire\" written by Jim Adler\n* \"Psy-Op + Cell + Merchant + Birds\" Teleplay by: Cindy Appel & Andrew Karlsruher; Story by: Stephanie Hicks & Andrew Klein\n* \"Save + The + Dam + World\" teleplay by Cindy Appel; story by Terry Matalas\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\nOn May 9, 2019, [[CBS]] renewed ''MacGyver'' for a thirteen episode fourth season that would air mid-season in the [[2019\u201320 United States network television schedule]].<ref name=\"S4Renewal\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/macgyver-renewed-season-4-cbs-1202605487/|title='MacGyver' Renewed For Season 4 By CBS|work=Deadline Hollywood|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|last2=Petski|first2=Denise|date=May 9, 2019|accessdate=May 9, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190509203603/https://deadline.com/2019/05/macgyver-renewed-season-4-cbs-1202605487/|archive-date=May 9, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> It was later revealed that the season would premiere on February 7, 2020.<ref name=\"S4Premiere\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/11/cbs-winter-schedule-midseason-criminal-minds-final-season-15-premiere-ncis-new-orleans-new-time-slot-survivor-season-40-undercover-boss-tommy-fbi-most-wanted-macgyver-premiere-date-1202782646/|title=CBS Sets Winter Schedule: \u2018Criminal Minds\u2019 Returns To Original Slot For Final Season, \u2018NCIS: New Orleans\u2019 Moves To Sunday|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=November 11, 2019|accessdate=November 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191218082224/https://deadline.com/2019/11/cbs-winter-schedule-midseason-criminal-minds-final-season-15-premiere-ncis-new-orleans-new-time-slot-survivor-season-40-undercover-boss-tommy-fbi-most-wanted-macgyver-premiere-date-1202782646/|archive-date=December 18, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On November 6, 2019, it was announced that nine additional episodes had been ordered bringing the season to a full season of twenty-two episodes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvseriesfinale.com/tv-show/macgyver-season-four-cbs-picks-up-nine-more-episodes/|title=MacGyver: Season Four; CBS Picks Up Nine More Episodes|last=Avalos|first=Regina|date=November 6, 2019|accessdate=December 26, 2019|work=TV Series Finale}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nThe series continues to be produced in [[Atlanta, Georgia]], filming at Mailing Avenue Stageworks in [[Chosewood Park]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/atlanta/news/2017/03/24/atlanta-filmed-macgyver-renewed-for-second-season.html|title=Atlanta-filmed 'MacGyver' renewed for second season|last=Hensley|first=Ellie|date=March 24, 2017|accessdate=February 28, 2019|work=[[Atlanta Business Chronicle]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190224041410/https://www.bizjournals.com/atlanta/news/2017/03/24/atlanta-filmed-macgyver-renewed-for-second-season.html|archive-date=February 24, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn March 13, 2020, it was announced that production on the fourth season had been shut down due to the [[2019-20 coronavirus pandemic]] reducing the season's original episode order from 22 to 20.\n\n===Casting===\nThe season features six starring roles, four of which returned from the first season. [[Levy Tran]] was promoted to series regular after recurring in the previous season. [[Henry Ian Cusick]] will also join the main cast.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2019/06/28/henry-ian-cusick-macgyver-season-4-series-regular/|title=Henry Ian Cusick Joins MacGyver Season 4 Cast as Master Manipulator|work=TVLine|last=Mitovich|first=Matt Webb|date=June 28, 2019|accessdate=June 28, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190628215907/https://tvline.com/2019/06/28/henry-ian-cusick-macgyver-season-4-series-regular/|archive-date=June 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical reception===\n\n\n===Ratings===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:99%\"\n|-\n! {{abbr|No.|Number}}\n! Title\n! Air date\n! [[Nielsen ratings|Rating]]<br>(18\u201349)\n! Viewers<br>(millions)\n! DVR<br>(18\u201349)\n! DVR viewers<br>(millions)\n! Total<br>(18\u201349)\n! Total viewers<br>(millions)\n{{Television Ratings Row/aired|February 8, 2020|1:00|1|[[#ep67|Fire + Ashes + Legacy = Phoenix]]|February 7, 2020|0.7|5.94<ref name=\"4.01\"/>|0.3|1.54|1.0|7.48}}\n{{Television Ratings Row/aired|February 15, 2020|1:00|2|[[#ep68|Red Cell + Quantu