nt)|Calvados]], [[France]]. They were also [[Lord of the Manor|Lords of the Manor]] of [[Stogursey]], [[Somerset]]. Lord Kingsale died in sheltered housing in Somerset, where he had lived since 1994, on 15 September 2005 aged 64.\n\nHe was succeeded in his peerages by a descendant of the 20th Baron, Nevinson Mark de Courcy, who was born 11 May 1958.\n\nHe had [[British North America]]n roots through his ancestor John de Courcy, 25th Baron Kingsale (c. 1717\u20131776), who was born in [[Rhode Island]].\n\n==Ancestry==\n{{ahnentafel\n|collapsed=yes |align=center\n|boxstyle_1=background-color: #fcc;\n|boxstyle_2=background-color: #fb9;\n|boxstyle_3=background-color: #ffc;\n|boxstyle_4=background-color: #bfc;\n|boxstyle_5=background-color: #9fe;\n|1= 1. '''John de Courcy, 35th Baron Kingsale'''\n|2= 2. The Hon. Michael de Courcy\n|3= 3.  Joan Reid\n|4= 4. Michael de Courcy, 34th Baron Kingsale\n|5= 5. Constance Mary Ranc\u00e9 Woodhouse\n|6= 6. Robert Reid\n|7= 7. \n|8= 8. Michael de Courcy, 33rd Baron Kingsale\n|9= 9. Emily Frances Anne de Courcy\n|10= 10. Tom Percy Woodhouse\n|11= 11. \n|12= 12. \n|13= 13. \n|14= 14. \n|15= 15. \n|16= 16. Michael de Courcy, 32nd Baron Kingsale\n|17= 17. Esther Eleanor Williams\n|18= 18. William Sinclair de Courcy\n|19= 19. \n|20= 20. \n|21= 21. \n|22= 22. \n|23= 23. \n|24= 24. \n|25= 25. \n|26= 26. \n|27= 27. \n|28= 28. \n|29= 29.\n|30= 30. \n|31= 31. \n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n* {{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/main.jhtml?view=DETAILS&grid=&xml=/news/2005/09/22/db2201.xml |via=King's Mead School |title=Obituary - John de Courcy |archiveurl=http://www.kingsmeadschool.co.uk/decourcyobituary.htm |archivedate=23 September 2005 |date=22 September 2005}}\n* [https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/the-sorry-tale-of-an-aristocrat-on-his-uppers-1594968.html The Independent:The Sorry Tale of an Aristocrat on his Uppers]\n\n==External links==\n*http://www.thepeerage.com/p29951.htm#i299510 de Courcy ancestry\n{{s-